  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 32-year-old man, who is a construction worker, presents 4 hours after falling from scaffolding and landing on his outstretched right hand. Examination shows significant swelling of the wrist and forearm with intact neurovascular status. Radiographs show a closed, displaced distal radius fracture that was successfully reduced under procedural sedation. The patient reports increasing pain despite reduction. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Apply a circumferential short-arm cast for optimal immobilization"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Apply a volar splint extending to the metacarpals"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Apply a sugar tong forearm splint with adequate padding"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Use a prefabricated wrist brace"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Defer immobilization and reassess in 24 hours"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Circumferential <span data-sememe-id=\"Efd8L60\">casting</span> is contraindicated in acute injuries with significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SM0yLg&anker=Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-learningcard-id=\"SM0yLg\" data-anker=\"Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-section-id=\"JcXsWC\" data-sememe-id=\"Oo0IXS\">edema</a>, because it increases the risk of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=330SRf&anker=Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"330SRf\" data-anker=\"Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-section-id=\"F4agOk\" data-sememe-id=\"gO0F7T\">compartment syndrome</a> and other pressure-related complications. This patient's significant swelling and increasing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> despite reduction indicate a high risk for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=330SRf&anker=Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"330SRf\" data-anker=\"Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-section-id=\"F4agOk\" data-sememe-id=\"gO0F7T\">compartment syndrome</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z88382058cc3200e6fee5365f12fb9315\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z88382058cc3200e6fee5365f12fb9315\" data-section-id=\"VxXGvZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"UTdbJ60\">volar splint</a> is specifically contraindicated for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">distal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TF06h3&anker=Z3095cf308256bc83c05476d4d6045efd\" data-learningcard-id=\"TF06h3\" data-anker=\"Z3095cf308256bc83c05476d4d6045efd\">radial fractures</a> because it does not limit <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zbd8adc50836aaba960773ef3c6f8a4d1\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zbd8adc50836aaba960773ef3c6f8a4d1\" data-section-id=\"M6cMlW0\" data-sememe-id=\"GjcBbc0\">pronation</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zfad6bd9df466928854884d9f8bed0486\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zfad6bd9df466928854884d9f8bed0486\" data-section-id=\"M6cMlW0\" data-sememe-id=\"sjctbc0\">supination</a> of the wrist, which is necessary for proper <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"aTdQ660\">immobilization</a>. Additionally, it does not provide adequate stabilization for this type of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z80700d0adbadd455ff75407de5f7921d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z80700d0adbadd455ff75407de5f7921d\" data-section-id=\"VxXGvZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"4jd30J0\">sugar tong forearm splint</a> is the appropriate choice for mid forearm and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">distal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=TF06h3&anker=Z3095cf308256bc83c05476d4d6045efd\" data-learningcard-id=\"TF06h3\" data-anker=\"Z3095cf308256bc83c05476d4d6045efd\">forearm fractures</a>, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=O30Iif&anker=Zb54b9ab6d0310ce84649ce755fa02f5b\" data-learningcard-id=\"O30Iif\" data-anker=\"Zb54b9ab6d0310ce84649ce755fa02f5b\">distal radius fractures</a>. This <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splint</span> accommodates injury-related swelling better than circumferential casts, reducing the risk of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=330SRf&anker=Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"330SRf\" data-anker=\"Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-section-id=\"F4agOk\" data-sememe-id=\"gO0F7T\">compartment syndrome</a>. It prevents forearm <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zbd8adc50836aaba960773ef3c6f8a4d1\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zbd8adc50836aaba960773ef3c6f8a4d1\" data-section-id=\"M6cMlW0\" data-sememe-id=\"GjcBbc0\">pronation</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zfad6bd9df466928854884d9f8bed0486\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zfad6bd9df466928854884d9f8bed0486\" data-section-id=\"M6cMlW0\" data-sememe-id=\"sjctbc0\">supination</a> while allowing for swelling, making it ideal for the management of acute <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> involving significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SM0yLg&anker=Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-learningcard-id=\"SM0yLg\" data-anker=\"Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-section-id=\"JcXsWC\" data-sememe-id=\"Oo0IXS\">edema</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Prefabricated <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splints</span> provide limited customization options and less effective <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"aTdQ660\">immobilization</a> compared to custom-made <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splints</span>. They are not intended for immobilizing reduced <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a>, making them inappropriate for this patient.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Delaying <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"aTdQ660\">immobilization</a> is inappropriate because all suspected acute extremity <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a> should be immobilized immediately to control <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> and prevent complications. This patient's increasing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> suggests potential <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=330SRf&anker=Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"330SRf\" data-anker=\"Zbd387d6535912cbe5ff7e51d6d2c8bbf\" data-section-id=\"F4agOk\" data-sememe-id=\"gO0F7T\">compartment syndrome</a> development, making immediate and appropriate splinting even more critical.</div>",
